    "narrative": "For April 10, **Mickey Moniak** (75.98) and **Brice Turang** (75.06) headline our daily efficiency ratings, both benefiting from highly favorable matchups against right-handed starters with vulnerable xERAs. **Mickey Moniak** is positioned for a breakout day; his score is significantly elevated by a +14% platoon edge against Walker Buehler and an additional +2% boost from Buehler\u2019s slow delivery, which provides a prime environment for his wheels to impact the SB category. Similarly, **Brice Turang** earns top billing via a massive +19% SP skill adjustment against Jake Irvin and a prime leadoff spot that maximizes his run-scoring potential. **Vinnie Pasquantino** (72.92) rounds out our offensive core, utilizing a +17% SP skill boost and a +14% platoon advantage against Davis Martin to solidify his status as a high-floor utility play.\n\nThe most difficult decision on the periphery was the exclusion of **Jose Caballero** (53.26), who narrowly missed the starting cut. While **Jose Caballero** benefits from a positive platoon split against the lefty Steven Matz, his offensive output is capped by a projected bottom-of-the-order assignment that drags his efficiency below the threshold of our starting nine. Conversely, **Corbin Carroll** (55.87) remains in the lineup despite a sub-optimal matchup against the high-skill Jes\u00fas Luzardo; his inclusion is a strategic hedge, as his elite speed profile remains essential for our league-wide emphasis on stolen bases. Owners should exercise caution regarding **Dalton Rushing**, **Gabriel Moreno**, and the rest of the bottom half of the lineup, as these scores rely on \"Lineup Pending\" assumptions; confirmed orders could shift these valuations significantly if these players are pushed further down the lineup.",
